The paper deals with algorithms for generating well-spaced points and approximate Delaunay graphs, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm also involves maintaining a Voronoi diagram and storing a superset of Delaunay neighbors, which are data structures commonly used in computational geometry and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions producing a hierarchically well-spaced superset, which is a technique used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the running time of the algorithm, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
